<!-- TITLE:> The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy  -->
<!-- DATE:> 2014-03-08 -->
<!-- CATAGORIES:> book review -->
<!-- SUMMARY:> My review of the first book in the famous sci-fi series by Douglas Adams.-->

<div class="outer-main">
	<div class="inner-main">
		<h4 align="right">2014 - 03 - 08</h3>
		<h2>The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy</h2>
		<h4 align="left">~33 seconds <a class="h4" href="http://fogg.me.uk/blog/reading">reading</a></h3>
		<article>
			<p><em>Read: 2nd-7th August 2013</em></p>

			<p>Just finished the book and my first thought was that I should have read it sooner. For about three years now it's been on my reading list and I should have just jumped it to the top. It's not really like any other book I've raid in its style and it was definitely a good one to end my reading hiatus with. Very funny but clever with it's humour too – I'm certainly looking forward to reading the sequels.</p>

			<p>I'll probably leave some other books in-between them so that I don't finish the entire series in one go. I get the feeling it's going to be one I wish will go on forever.</p>
		</article>
		<br class="small">
